<h1>Problem 837 - 2021 MODSMO, P5 of 7, AN</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Does there exist an infinite sequence \(P_{1}(x), P_{2}(x), P_{3}(x), \ldots\) of integer polynomials, all of degree \(1000,\) such that for each integer \(z\) there is a unique natural number \(i\) and integer \(x\) for which \(P_{i}(x)=z\)?</p>
